objects.name: cheeky chipmunk
objects.description: Cheeky Chipmunk is a malicious Microsoft Windows RPC server installed via a PowerShell loader. It is tasked by a separate RPC client and can execute shell commands, upload, and download files.

objects.name: Cheeky Chipmunk
objects.description: The threat actor behind the Cheeky Chipmunk malware, assessed to be of medium sophistication.

objects.name: CVE-2021-44228
objects.description: Not directly mentioned in the report, but a CVE example is given.

objects.name: CheekyChipmunk_command_argument_check
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule CheekyChipmunk_command_argument_check { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects Cheeky Chipmunk argument checking code to determine command to process. " date = "2022-01-24" hash1 = "7e4a6bac09ad214e98801bc199f96c265d7b6b48" strings: $1 = {66 83 F8 70 75 ?? C7 85 ?? FD FF FF 01 00 00 00 EB ??} condition: uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and uint32(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x00004550 and all of them }

objects.name: T1543.003
objects.description: Cheeky Chipmunk maintains persistence by adding a new Windows service (pnrsp) for the RPC server component.

objects.name: T1059.001
objects.description: Open-source PowerShell runner code is embedded in the Cheeky Chipmunk RPC server and used to invoke commands stored in the registry.

objects.name: T1059.003
objects.description: The Cheeky Chipmunk RPC server can be sent Windows shell commands by the RPC client.

objects.name: T1559.001
objects.description: The Cheeky Chipmunk RPC server uses COM to call embedded PowerShell runner code.

objects.name: T1047
objects.description: Cheeky Chipmunk implements an RPC server to receive tasking.

objects.name: T1140
objects.description: The Cheeky Chipmunk loader uses built-in and open-source PowerShell libraries to Base64-decode, 3DES-decrypt, and GZIP-decompress the RPC server.

objects.name: T1070.004
objects.description: The Cheeky Chipmunk loader is deleted from disk once the RPC server is running.

objects.name: T1036.005
objects.description: Cheeky Chipmunk masquerades as a legitimate Windows service path (netsvcs) to maintain persistence.

objects.name: T1027
objects.description: Cheeky Chipmunk's import names are obfuscated by XORing with 0x55.

objects.name: T1562.001
objects.description: Cheeky Chipmunk implements an AMSI bypass technique.

objects.name: T1005
objects.description: Cheeky Chipmunk can be tasked to collect files.
